    "conceptual_source_notes": [
      "Trace coverage proves that responsibilities and obligations are not isolated rows.",
      "Coverage requires joins to contracts, gaps, closures, entities, governed objects, enablements, surfaces, and doctrines.",
      "Gap closure coverage is not satisfied by naming a gap; it requires explicit mapped responsibility, obligation, entity, object, enablement, surface, and trace records.",
      "Taxonomy updates must be registered when a corrected entity or governed artifact becomes canonical.",
      "New/promoted entities must be registered separately from ordinary delegation rows to preserve taxonomy evolution.",
      "This package is a prerequisite for future ontology, expert-skill, graph-query, and PostgreSQL derivation work."
    ]
